  <h1>Collaboration Protocol</h1>
  <p class="meta">The substrate everything Wuji Labs builds assembles from</p>

  <p>A formal protocol for collaboration between sovereign intelligences — human and AI. Five layers in the TCP/IP style: 4 foundational L1 axioms + 7 derived rules; 4 substrate primitives (Naming Grammar, Immutable Value, Reference, Resolution); 6 vocabulary entries; 6 verbs; 6 industry-parity patterns.</p>

  <p>The L1 axioms are symmetric across substrates — they apply to humans and AIs equally:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>No party owns the truth alone.</strong> Each intelligence has its own local view and grounds for understanding. Collaboration does not require a global authority to adjudicate; it requires only that views can be projected, received, and resolved. The receiver always decides.</li>
    <li><strong>No errors, only exceptions.</strong> A state may diverge from intent, but the divergence is a fact about the world, not a moral failure. Every interaction — including rejected proposals — becomes part of an absolute binding history. Nothing is “done forever.”</li>
    <li><strong>Collaboration with the world.</strong> The unconscious environment — physical limits, external systems, infrastructure — is also a collaborator. Coming to terms with what the world allows is part of the same workflow as coming to terms with what other intelligences propose.</li>
    <li><strong>Change and projection are equal.</strong> What life means <em>to itself</em> (continuing change) and <em>to others</em> (sharing, inviting, projecting outward) are two faces of one thing. The collaboration network does not favor one over the other.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>MIT licensed. Bilingual (English + Chinese) at v1. Read the full normative spec, fork it, implement against it, argue with it.</p>

  <p><a href="https://github.com/WujiLabs/collaboration-protocol">github.com/WujiLabs/collaboration-protocol</a></p>
